ls, and movie scripts, petitions to leaders from intellectuals, and secret police reports on intellectuals under surveillance. Introductions, explanatory materials, and a biographical index accompany the documents.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCommunism and culturezSoviet UnionxHistoryvSources. 0aCommunism and intellectualszSoviet UnionxHistoryvSources. 0aPolitics and culturezSoviet UnionxHistoryvSources. 0aPolitics and literaturezSoviet UnionxHistoryvSources. 0aPower (Social sciences)zSoviet UnionxHistoryvSources. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300150001423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300150001.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles